Part I - (Ford gobike trip)¶

by (NGWAM ALFRED NIYAH)¶

Introduction¶

The dataset Ford gobike trip is data that comes to replace the traditional bike renting scheme to a new generation of an automatic bike renting scheme. Through this system users are able to easily rent bike from a particular position and return it back to another position.Intrestingly, they exist a great interest in these system due to it important role in traffic, environmental and health issues.

Problem Statement¶

There has been huge amount of data generated in this scheme.However,in understanding which among the listed variables plays a vital role in ensuring efficiency in this scheme the need to for analysing data and point vital questions such as : Which age category were more into the bike sharing scheme? which user type were less involved into the scheme? Which gender were toping the scheme and deeping down to which among were less time to arrive their destinations ? Which period of the day were people more into the scheme? As a proposed solution, I will be analysing the member birth year, gender, user type,duration,hours of the day, to see how these factors influenced the customer' choice

def his_function(ticks,bins,df):
    plt.hist(df,bins = bins)
    plt.title('duration in minutes distribution')
    plt.xlabel('duration(minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xscale('log')
    plt.xticks(ticks,ticks)
    plt.show()
    
    
    
bins = 10**np.arange(0,3+0.15,0.1)
ticks = [1,3,10,30,100,300,1000]
df=df['duration_mins']
show = his_function(ticks,bins,df)

This visualization shows a clear and easy to interpret as the bins are normaly distributed and giving a high frequency at a time of 10mins.
